VoiceMap.Text: Ok, we have your first patient. It looks pretty straightforward, but we're going to take you through it with lots of help. Go ahead and start by getting an airway an breathing assessment.
No matter what's going wrong, you need to verify you have a good airway. Your resident can help you with that.
Remember... A, B, C. How's his breathing?
How's the patient's circulation? What are our vitals?
Let's start with an AMPLE and then complete your secondary survey. You can ask your resident to examine the head, neck, back, pelvis, and extremities.
We should address this leg wound, Doctor. How about some pressure on the wound and a suture kit?
So what do you think Doctor? Are we admitting or discharging Mr. Benson?
